WEBVTT

02:08.750 --> 02:11.875
(DANCE MUSIC PLAYING)

02:13.458 --> 02:16.583
(LIVELY CHATTER)

02:41.125 --> 02:43.500
There's no line right now
if you want to get another.

02:43.583 --> 02:45.917
I didn't know we were getting
drunk tonight.

02:47.500 --> 02:49.458
I'm getting drunk tonight.

02:49.542 --> 02:51.375
You're more than welcome
to join in.

02:51.458 --> 02:53.583
You can blog hung over,
you know?

03:02.667 --> 03:04.041
Maybe we should just go.

03:04.125 --> 03:05.750
I don't know.
I thought we could dance.

03:05.834 --> 03:07.125
Don't you think
that sounds fun?

03:12.000 --> 03:13.667
Do you not want
to be here anymore?

03:16.333 --> 03:18.000
I could text some people.

03:18.792 --> 03:20.333
Can I finish
my drink at least?

03:22.333 --> 03:23.875
I'm gonna go get your coat.

03:43.583 --> 03:44.834
(SIGHS)

03:44.917 --> 03:46.417
I just wish
they would respond.

03:46.500 --> 03:49.250
They said
the notification date for
accepted prose was noon today.

03:49.333 --> 03:50.625
Fuck.

03:50.709 --> 03:52.125
I'm trying to figure out
a good way

03:52.208 --> 03:56.125
to describe Berlin
in under 140 characters.

03:56.208 --> 03:57.709
For the Internet?

03:58.375 --> 04:00.667
No, for right now.

04:07.000 --> 04:08.291
We're taken.

04:08.375 --> 04:10.166
(SCOFFS) I'd hope so.

04:10.250 --> 04:14.291
Leah, this is Beau.
We've been dating for one year
and three months.

04:14.375 --> 04:16.333
So this is the famous Leah.

04:16.416 --> 04:17.959
Do I curtsy now?

04:18.041 --> 04:20.041
You'd have to stand up
to do that.

04:21.416 --> 04:22.834
Mmm.

04:22.917 --> 04:25.166
Well, I was living in Europe.

04:25.250 --> 04:28.333
There's a party at a friend
of a friend of Amy's.

04:28.417 --> 04:33.000
If you do decide to stay,
my friend Dan just ordered
a lot of coke.

04:33.834 --> 04:35.000
Really?

04:35.083 --> 04:36.000
Hmm.

04:36.083 --> 04:38.125
I guess we're staying now.

04:39.250 --> 04:40.000
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

04:40.083 --> 04:44.000
(SIREN BLARING IN DISTANCE)

05:05.542 --> 05:06.875
PAUL: 2.1 miles.

05:08.333 --> 05:09.917
That's how far the city is.

05:15.834 --> 05:18.125
Google maps.

05:19.125 --> 05:21.375
-Siri.
-(CHUCKLES)

05:24.291 --> 05:24.542
Wait, really?

05:26.041 --> 05:28.792
(CHUCKLES) No. No.

05:28.875 --> 05:30.417
Erin, actually. Erin Bower.

05:32.792 --> 05:33.875
First and last.

05:34.000 --> 05:34.500
(CHUCKLES) I like that.

05:37.000 --> 05:38.166
Paul Chen.

05:40.333 --> 05:42.333
(GASPS) For real?

05:43.208 --> 05:44.333
Oh, I'm... I'm sorry.
That was rude.

05:44.417 --> 05:46.000
I didn't mean this
to be an interrogation.

05:46.083 --> 05:48.375
I... It's not like I...

05:48.458 --> 05:49.750
I do... I do know who you are.

05:49.834 --> 05:52.917
I mean, I've heard your name
around a lot, I guess. I...

05:53.000 --> 05:54.583
I haven't read
your book, but...

05:54.667 --> 05:55.917
I mean, I... I want to.

05:56.000 --> 05:59.291
I've... I've heard
it's really, really great.
(SIGHS)

06:00.417 --> 06:03.542
(GROANS) Can I start over?

06:03.625 --> 06:07.750
I didn't mean to convey
displeasure to you by frowning
like that. It's just...

06:07.834 --> 06:10.667
I had a reading earlier
and I took a few bars of...

06:11.667 --> 06:13.750
-Yeah. It's put me
in a weird mood.
-(CHUCKLES)

06:13.834 --> 06:17.625
That's okay. I'm, like,
always in a weird mood.

06:17.709 --> 06:22.417
Huh. Seems like we can come
to some kind of understanding.

06:23.542 --> 06:24.959
I'll draw up the deal memo.

06:25.041 --> 06:27.208
My secretary
will fax it to you.

06:27.291 --> 06:27.875
What are the terms?

06:27.959 --> 06:31.208
Quite favorable.

06:31.291 --> 06:32.458
(CHUCKLES)

06:33.083 --> 06:34.208
Oh.

06:34.875 --> 06:36.959
Hello.

06:39.125 --> 06:40.500
No, I think you have
the wrong number.

06:42.875 --> 06:45.333
It's a... It's a joke.

06:45.792 --> 06:47.458
No one called me.

06:47.542 --> 06:50.125
-(CHUCKLES)
-No...

06:50.208 --> 06:53.959
-BEAU:
You're always vanishing.
-(SCOFFS) Oh, please.

06:54.041 --> 06:55.458
-(CHUCKLES) What?
-No.

06:55.542 --> 06:57.625
-Did I make you angry?
-(SIGHS)

06:57.709 --> 07:00.917
It was good to meet you, Erin.
I'm gonna head back inside.

07:01.000 --> 07:03.875
-Yeah. Um...
-(PAUL AND ERIN CHUCKLE)

07:03.959 --> 07:08.875
Uh, have your secretary
drop off the deal memo.

07:08.959 --> 07:11.792
Oh, yeah. Yeah. I'll have it
notarized ASAP.

07:11.875 --> 07:14.166
-I'd really like that.
-Okay.

07:17.834 --> 07:20.041
What?

07:20.125 --> 07:21.458
(SIGHS)

07:22.250 --> 07:23.875
Is he from a magazine?

07:26.959 --> 07:27.583
ERIN: Beau, slow down!

07:29.375 --> 07:29.667
Beau, slow...

07:31.625 --> 07:34.667
Beau! Beau...
Beau, please slow down.

07:34.750 --> 07:36.458
Beau, please!

07:36.542 --> 07:37.625
Can you...

07:37.709 --> 07:39.667
Can you... Can you tell me
what's going on? I mean,

07:39.750 --> 07:41.875
you're acting bizarre
all night.

07:43.208 --> 07:43.709
I'm on drugs.

07:46.583 --> 07:48.625
Oh, was it worth it?

07:48.709 --> 07:50.375
Are you having fun?

07:52.291 --> 07:53.667
You should sleep
at your place tonight.

07:56.458 --> 07:58.208
I can't have
this conversation right now.

07:58.291 --> 07:59.750
I'm way too fucked up.

07:59.834 --> 08:02.583
Why does it feel like
if I go now, things are
gonna be over?

08:06.500 --> 08:07.875
Maybe they are.

08:10.000 --> 08:11.917
What... Are you...

08:12.583 --> 08:13.917
Are you breaking...

08:14.000 --> 08:14.709
Are you breaking up with me?

08:16.750 --> 08:19.291
No. Just...

08:19.375 --> 08:21.917
-(CELL PHONE CHIMES)
-Felt like that's what I was
supposed to say there.

08:25.667 --> 08:28.542
Are you fucking serious?
Oh, my...

08:29.333 --> 08:31.792
-Fucking asshole!
-Erin! Please...

08:50.959 --> 08:53.333
MAN: Uh, these need
to be cataloged.

08:53.417 --> 08:56.500
Guy who dropped them off
said one or two
are first editions.

08:56.583 --> 08:57.959
Okay, I'm on it.

08:58.041 --> 08:58.875
MAN: Is this any good?

08:58.959 --> 09:01.250
Oh. Uh...

09:01.333 --> 09:05.291
Actually, I was thinking
we could book him in
for a reading.

09:05.375 --> 09:07.625
He's been doing a bunch
around the city.

09:07.709 --> 09:08.792
You know him?

09:08.875 --> 09:12.542
Well, not super well,
but he's a friend.

09:12.625 --> 09:12.792
Huh.

09:14.625 --> 09:15.792
Hey, uh...

09:15.875 --> 09:18.667
Erin, I've been meaning
to talk to you
about something.

09:18.750 --> 09:19.750
Okay.

09:19.834 --> 09:23.166
Things, um...
Things have been tight lately.

09:23.250 --> 09:26.792
Uh, long and short is,
I can't afford to keep
everyone on full-time.

09:26.875 --> 09:29.333
I'm gonna have to
cut your hours a bit.

09:29.709 --> 09:31.125
I'm sorry.

09:33.125 --> 09:35.291
(SIGHS) It's... It's fine.

09:36.041 --> 09:38.125
I mean, more time
to write, right?

09:39.875 --> 09:40.667
ERIN: Waking up at 3:00 a.m.

09:42.709 --> 09:45.333
I wonder if it can
really be possible

09:45.417 --> 09:48.000
that I've gone through
25 years of my life now

09:48.083 --> 09:51.750
without forming a truly
genuine connection
to another person.

09:51.834 --> 09:55.041
The kind of connection
where you know instantly

09:55.125 --> 09:59.500
what that other person
is thinking
at any given moment,

09:59.583 --> 10:03.417
and where that horrible,
mysterious gulf
between the two of you

10:03.500 --> 10:06.041
is permanently bridged.

10:06.125 --> 10:11.000
The dissolution of
subject-object connection.

10:11.083 --> 10:13.166
The way you know
what they'll say
in telekinetic advance.

10:13.250 --> 10:18.333
The way a writer knows
her character's next desire
she must repress.

10:19.333 --> 10:20.750
Her unpublished need
still met.

10:23.417 --> 10:23.750
A finger.

10:26.250 --> 10:27.458
Key.

10:28.625 --> 10:30.000
Connection.

10:31.792 --> 10:33.333
Muscle memory.

10:34.792 --> 10:36.125
Muscle memory.

10:37.208 --> 10:39.542
Muscle memory.

10:42.959 --> 10:46.250
PAUL: There were times
when his memory

10:46.333 --> 10:51.542
like an external hard drive
that had been taken from him

10:51.625 --> 10:56.583
and hidden inside
an unwieldy series
of cardboard boxes.

10:57.458 --> 11:00.375
Or placed at the end

11:00.458 --> 11:03.875
of a long and dark
and messy corridor.

11:03.959 --> 11:07.792
Required much more effort
than he felt

11:07.875 --> 11:08.792
motivated to exert

11:10.375 --> 11:12.000
simply to locate.

11:13.667 --> 11:13.875
In fact,

11:16.041 --> 11:19.542
he felt increasingly
unmotivated

11:19.625 --> 11:23.083
to exert any effort
towards anything.

11:29.500 --> 11:30.750
(MAN COUGHS)

11:32.000 --> 11:33.166
(GULPS)

11:34.500 --> 11:35.917
(APPLAUSE)

11:42.583 --> 11:42.917
Any questions?

11:44.959 --> 11:46.625
Uh, can you hear me?

11:48.500 --> 11:50.041
-Yeah.
-Good.

11:50.125 --> 11:52.375
Do you even know
how to grow mushrooms?

11:52.917 --> 11:54.500
Mushrooms?

11:54.583 --> 11:56.291
Yeah, in your book
you take mushrooms.

11:56.375 --> 11:58.333
Do you know how
to grow them, sir?

11:59.542 --> 12:00.750
Not really.

12:02.917 --> 12:04.458
I have a problem with you.

12:04.542 --> 12:08.792
Classifying your books
as fiction when they're
obviously about you,

12:08.875 --> 12:10.583
doesn't that make it
a memoir?

12:10.667 --> 12:14.166
-(SCATTERED CLAP)
-If I wrote a memoir,

12:16.959 --> 12:17.834
I would call it my memoir.

12:20.041 --> 12:22.792
I also would write

12:22.875 --> 12:26.959
"I think" before
every sentence.

12:27.041 --> 12:29.458
You can't pretend
something is fiction.

12:29.542 --> 12:32.500
Either it's based on your
experience or it's not.

12:32.583 --> 12:33.959
But why can't he?

12:34.041 --> 12:36.500
He's the one
who writes it, right?

12:36.583 --> 12:38.583
(SCATTERED APPLAUSE)

12:40.542 --> 12:42.667
(UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING)

12:45.000 --> 12:46.291
You saved me.

12:48.250 --> 12:48.917
I am forever
in your debt.

12:51.500 --> 12:54.458
Are people at your readings
always this weird?

12:54.542 --> 12:57.667
Yes. That's why I have to
take sedatives before them.

12:57.750 --> 13:00.792
Uh, you're on drugs
at all of your readings?
(CHUCKLES)

13:00.875 --> 13:03.625
-Do you want some?
-(SIGHS)

13:05.583 --> 13:07.625
I think it's cool
you work in a bookstore.

13:08.542 --> 13:11.208
Is that a sentence
from your memoir?

13:12.166 --> 13:13.750
It's a hyperlink to
the question of,

13:13.834 --> 13:16.500
"What else do you do
when you're not
in this bookstore?"

13:16.583 --> 13:19.375
I write. Well, blog.

13:19.458 --> 13:21.583
God, that's embarrassing
to tell you. (CHUCKLES)

13:21.667 --> 13:23.834
-What's it called?
-Mmm.

13:23.917 --> 13:26.667
Here. It's, uh...
It's on Tumblr.

13:26.750 --> 13:28.291
Um, can you hold this?

13:28.667 --> 13:30.291
(BAG CLATTERING)

13:35.000 --> 13:36.333
(KEYS CLATTER)

13:37.208 --> 13:38.375
(SIGHS)

13:42.625 --> 13:44.959
"I don't want to sleep
but I don't know
what I'm waiting for."

13:47.959 --> 13:50.458
-That's a nice name.
-(CHUCKLES)

13:51.041 --> 13:52.125
Modern.

13:53.291 --> 13:54.834
Actually, I already
knew about it.

13:56.834 --> 13:58.667
(WHISPERS) I googled you.

13:58.750 --> 14:00.333
(CHUCKLES) You googled me?

14:00.834 --> 14:02.291
CALVIN: Paul! Yo.

14:05.792 --> 14:08.709
We met a couple
months ago.

14:08.792 --> 14:09.959
Kyle's friend. Calvin.

14:11.542 --> 14:13.208
Oh, yeah. Calvin.

14:15.083 --> 14:19.208
(CHUCKLES) Um, anyway,
I, uh... I didn't know
you were a writer.

14:19.291 --> 14:22.583
But, uh, my girlfriend,
Mag... Maggie...

14:22.667 --> 14:26.125
-Maggie... Maggie is a big
fan of your books.
-(CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY)

14:26.208 --> 14:28.792
And so we came out,

14:28.875 --> 14:31.500
and I was like,
"Oh, fuck, it's Paul."
(CHUCKLES)

14:31.834 --> 14:33.208
So, yeah.

14:33.291 --> 14:36.166
I read all your books

14:36.250 --> 14:38.417
when I was in San Francisco
two years ago.

14:38.500 --> 14:40.166
I was really manic.
They helped.

14:40.250 --> 14:42.750
Um, I told all my friends

14:42.834 --> 14:45.333
that, uh, I had this feeling
when I came here,

14:45.417 --> 14:47.375
um, we're gonna meet
and become friends.

14:47.458 --> 14:49.000
CALVIN: Okay, baby, don't.

14:49.083 --> 14:53.166
Anyway, um, (CHUCKLES)
I was wondering if maybe
you wanna come tonight,

14:53.250 --> 14:56.542
uh, to my parents' mansion
in Jersey. I'm having
some friends over.

14:57.125 --> 14:59.500
Your parents' mansion?

14:59.583 --> 15:01.959
-Yeah.
-Like a really big house.

15:02.041 --> 15:03.709
There's a foyer.

15:03.792 --> 15:07.291
-Do you want to go
to a mansion in New Jersey?
-Oh, I don't know. I can't...

15:07.375 --> 15:09.291
We... We... We can drive.
We have a car.

15:09.375 --> 15:12.083
Um, (CHUCKLES) well,
Calvin can drive.
I can't drive.

15:12.166 --> 15:14.709
-Actually,
it's a really funny story.
-Maggie, don't do that.

15:14.792 --> 15:16.625
When I was in San Francisco
and I was manic,

15:16.709 --> 15:20.625
-and I stole my ex-boyfriend's
ca... Um... (EXCLAIMS)
-CALVIN: Okay, don't.

15:20.709 --> 15:23.333
-MAGGIE: Yeah. Yeah.
-You should come.

15:23.417 --> 15:25.458
(CHUCKLES) Okay.

15:25.542 --> 15:28.000
(MELLOW MUSIC PLAYING
ON SPEAKERS)

15:34.250 --> 15:37.500
Do you mind signing this?

15:37.583 --> 15:38.792
CALVIN: Maggie...

15:40.333 --> 15:41.041
I don't sign
that book anymore.

15:42.417 --> 15:43.625
Oh.

15:44.250 --> 15:45.583
(MAGGIE CHUCKLES)

15:48.458 --> 15:50.792
(CHUCKLES)

15:53.417 --> 15:55.166
-Do you have a pen?
-Always.

16:01.625 --> 16:04.625
I almost thought
you were gonna pull out
a computer.

16:04.709 --> 16:06.959
And I was surprised
it was actually a pen.

16:08.291 --> 16:09.458
(CHUCKLES)

16:10.125 --> 16:11.458
You're so funny.

16:14.875 --> 16:16.583
Maggie, we went
to a book-signing.

16:16.667 --> 16:18.083
That's a much
more perfect time...

16:18.166 --> 16:19.375
I have a surprise for you.

16:19.458 --> 16:21.333
(CALVIN AND MAGGIE CHATTERING)

16:21.417 --> 16:22.625
(CHUCKLES) What?

16:25.083 --> 16:26.750
(CHUCKLES) What's this?

16:28.959 --> 16:30.792
PAUL: I got it
from your store.

16:31.625 --> 16:33.375
You bought it for me?

16:33.458 --> 16:36.000
They probably
don't pay you enough.
You're owed a gift.

16:37.458 --> 16:39.250
Oh. Oh, you...

16:40.041 --> 16:41.667
Do you accept?

16:41.750 --> 16:43.542
(CHUCKLES) I accept.

16:57.500 --> 16:59.625
(CLOCK TICKING)

17:11.500 --> 17:13.290
Are you sure you want to?

17:14.165 --> 17:16.250
I don't wanna be

17:16.333 --> 17:17.625
corrupting an innocent
or anything.

17:17.709 --> 17:20.208
Oh, no. You... You are.

17:21.666 --> 17:23.250
You definitely are.

17:27.583 --> 17:28.667
Here.

17:29.542 --> 17:32.417
It's good shit.
My friend, Jasper,

17:32.500 --> 17:35.125
makes it on his houseboat
in Red Hook.

17:35.709 --> 17:36.959
Hmm.

17:37.250 --> 17:38.375
Mags?

17:44.041 --> 17:45.083
Yes.

17:45.834 --> 17:47.000
(CHUCKLES)

17:51.792 --> 17:52.959
Yes.

17:55.208 --> 17:57.542
CALVIN: I'm really glad
you guys came.

17:58.792 --> 18:00.542
How long have you been dating?

18:00.625 --> 18:03.125
Oh, we're not...
We're not dating.

18:03.500 --> 18:05.083
Really?

18:05.166 --> 18:06.291
Really seemed like you were?

18:08.917 --> 18:11.542
And what about...
What about you guys?

18:11.625 --> 18:13.625
Oh, yeah. We've been dating
for two years,

18:13.709 --> 18:14.625
but we haven't
had sex in four months.

18:14.709 --> 18:17.291
CALVIN: Maggie...

18:17.375 --> 18:19.500
(CLOCK TICKING)

18:22.291 --> 18:23.875
Is it weird we're here?

18:25.542 --> 18:26.959
Why would it be weird?

18:31.834 --> 18:33.083
(LIGHTER CLICKS)

18:50.166 --> 18:51.333
(DEEP INHALE)

18:53.959 --> 18:56.709
(DEEP EXHALE)

19:17.917 --> 19:21.041
I wanted to put my hand
on your leg just now.

19:26.333 --> 19:27.709
Why didn't you?

19:34.959 --> 19:36.125
Now I did.

19:41.166 --> 19:42.291
-(LIGHTER CLICKS)
-(DEEP INHALE)

19:45.375 --> 19:47.083
(DEEP EXHALE)

19:56.166 --> 19:58.250
Do you wanna go
for a walk?

19:59.750 --> 20:01.542
Have you tried acid before?

20:02.375 --> 20:04.417
(SIGHS) Only once.

20:04.500 --> 20:06.583
And, um...

20:06.667 --> 20:12.000
I rode around on
a Toronto City bus
for five hours.

20:12.083 --> 20:15.458
Beau and I do drugs sometimes,
but it doesn't always feel
the same with him.

20:17.625 --> 20:19.625
Beau is that guy
at the party, right?

20:20.875 --> 20:22.208
(CHUCKLES) Yeah.

20:22.291 --> 20:24.750
Um, I was gonna

20:24.834 --> 20:26.709
call him my boyfriend,
but I don't think
that's true anymore.

20:26.792 --> 20:29.041
-We don't have to talk
about it if you don't want...
-Oh, no, no, no.

20:29.125 --> 20:34.458
It's just, um,
in a process of...

20:34.542 --> 20:35.458
-Recontextualizing?
-Reconstituting.

20:36.875 --> 20:38.458
(BOTH CHUCKLE)

20:38.542 --> 20:39.959
Renewing?

20:41.542 --> 20:42.875
(SIGHS)

20:44.709 --> 20:46.834
-Hey, look. We're in sync.
-(CHUCKLES)

20:48.291 --> 20:53.166
When I was in fifth grade,

20:53.250 --> 20:57.792
I used to wear purple
and put glitter on my eyes
every Friday,

20:58.417 --> 21:00.250
because I thought that...

21:01.291 --> 21:02.625
(SIGHS)

21:02.709 --> 21:07.333
...if the aliens came,
they'd see me
and they'd just...

21:08.792 --> 21:11.834
(CHUCKLES) They'd just, like,
take me away.

21:11.917 --> 21:13.667
That's neutrally good.

21:15.291 --> 21:16.542
Can I tweet that?

21:16.625 --> 21:18.917
(CHUCKLES) But I... I...

21:19.000 --> 21:22.166
-I said it.
-I'll just save it to drafts.

21:22.250 --> 21:23.834
Let me think about it.

21:23.917 --> 21:25.750
Where'd you think
they'd take you?

21:27.583 --> 21:28.834
Just away.

21:30.333 --> 21:31.500
(CHUCKLES) Anywhere.

21:33.542 --> 21:37.166
Um, when I was in
the fifth grade,

21:37.250 --> 21:39.000
I was on a plane...

21:40.792 --> 21:43.583
and I... I saw this brown dot.

21:43.667 --> 21:44.500
I thought it was a UFO.

21:45.792 --> 21:47.875
Um...

21:47.959 --> 21:52.208
I think, at first, I was aware
that I was faking it,

21:52.291 --> 21:53.917
but I think

21:54.000 --> 21:56.208
I convinced myself so hard

21:56.291 --> 21:59.041
that I made myself
forget that part.

21:59.125 --> 22:01.041
(BREATHILY) Did you
tell anyone you saw
a UFO?

22:01.125 --> 22:04.041
I didn't care if anyone knew.

22:04.125 --> 22:06.000
(GASPING)

22:07.959 --> 22:09.834
I was just like,
"I saw a UFO."

22:11.291 --> 22:14.792
I was extremely bored
back then. I was like
a bored robot.

22:14.875 --> 22:15.583
(GASPING)

22:18.542 --> 22:19.917
Hey, where you going?

22:20.333 --> 22:22.125
Hey, wait. Wait.

22:28.291 --> 22:30.834
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

22:30.917 --> 22:31.542
I'm sorry. I just...

22:33.500 --> 22:35.834
I had, like, this crazy

22:35.917 --> 22:38.583
rush of emotions,
and it's just like...

22:38.667 --> 22:41.917
Being here with you is...

22:42.000 --> 22:44.917
-I don't know
how to talk to you.
-Okay. Okay.

22:45.000 --> 22:48.041
I mean, you're just like
an idea. You're not...

22:48.125 --> 22:49.375
Okay. Okay. Just...
Just... Just breathe.

22:49.458 --> 22:52.417
-Okay? Just breathe.
-(BREATHILY) So weird.

22:52.500 --> 22:55.333
-Just breathe in.
Breathe. Breathe in.
-So weird.

22:56.000 --> 22:57.000
-(BREATHING DEEPLY)
-Okay.

22:57.083 --> 23:00.542
-In. In.
-So weird.

23:00.625 --> 23:02.208
-(EXHALES)
-Out.

23:02.709 --> 23:04.166
(COUGHS, CHUCKLES)

23:04.250 --> 23:07.375
-Is that better?
-You think...
You think I'm crazy.

23:07.959 --> 23:09.083
You...

23:18.375 --> 23:19.500
(LIVELY CHATTER)

23:23.083 --> 23:26.041
(UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING
ON SPEAKERS)

23:58.000 --> 24:01.250
(MUSIC CONTINUES)

25:07.333 --> 25:09.458
(MUSIC CONTINUES)

25:57.875 --> 25:59.834
Sometimes, I wonder
what the point is.

26:02.166 --> 26:04.500
Will anyone give a shit
in five years?

26:04.583 --> 26:05.750
(CLICKS TONGUE)
In two?

26:08.458 --> 26:11.417
There's a project
I've wanted to do for a while.

26:11.959 --> 26:13.208
Basically, I would

26:13.291 --> 26:15.709
document everything
that happened to me.

26:15.792 --> 26:17.250
Uh, livestream it,

26:17.333 --> 26:19.709
or maybe just record it
and edit it later.

26:22.375 --> 26:23.959
Make a movie about life.

26:25.709 --> 26:27.709
Wow. (CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

26:27.792 --> 26:31.375
Just, like, a collection
of unrelated scenes.

26:32.417 --> 26:34.291
But I never started.

26:34.375 --> 26:37.125
I think I might be
more likely

26:37.208 --> 26:38.500
to complete it if...

26:38.583 --> 26:40.500
If someone else
did it with me.

26:42.208 --> 26:43.959
-Me? (CHUCKLES)
-Yeah.

26:46.458 --> 26:48.667
It would just be
our lives, but we film it.

26:58.750 --> 27:02.250
-(BEEPING)
-(EXHALES) Okay.

27:03.083 --> 27:05.375
Just pretend
like it's not there.

27:07.291 --> 27:08.667
(CHUCKLES)

27:11.291 --> 27:12.375
Okay.

27:12.709 --> 27:14.375
(SNORTS)

27:21.458 --> 27:22.709
PAUL: You don't have to.

27:22.792 --> 27:25.041
No, if... If you want to,

27:25.917 --> 27:28.542
I want to. Yes.

27:30.166 --> 27:31.417
(SNORTS)

27:33.083 --> 27:34.375
(ERIN COUGHING)

27:38.208 --> 27:38.792
(SNIFFLES)

27:40.333 --> 27:42.041
(CLEARS THROAT)

27:42.125 --> 27:44.417
-PAUL: Greetings.
-(CHUCKLES)

27:44.500 --> 27:46.875
So, what scenes is our movie
going to have?

27:46.959 --> 27:49.583
First is "Heroin." We inject
each other with heroin.

27:49.667 --> 27:51.375
-Then work on...
-(EXCLAIMS)

27:51.458 --> 27:53.542
Then we work on stuff
on our laptop.

27:53.625 --> 27:55.250
Have you ever been in love?

27:56.166 --> 27:58.000
-Um...
-Or, no, okay, "Cocaine."

27:58.083 --> 27:59.500
We go to nightclubs and bars

27:59.583 --> 28:02.625
with no other plan
other than to snort cocaine
every 15 minutes.

28:02.709 --> 28:03.041
(CHUCKLES) That's great.

28:03.125 --> 28:05.500
(BEEPING)

28:07.291 --> 28:09.041
PAUL: Do you ever feel like
you're a robot?

28:09.125 --> 28:10.333
Like you're just on autopilot?

28:10.417 --> 28:12.625
ERIN: More than me
feeling like a robot,

28:12.709 --> 28:15.500
I feel like everyone
around me is one and
I'm the only one who isn't.

28:15.583 --> 28:17.667
Do you think I'm a robot?

28:17.750 --> 28:20.500
ERIN: (WHISPERS)
Check this box to prove
you're not a robot.

28:22.583 --> 28:24.250
-(CHUCKLES)
-You come up with one.

28:24.333 --> 28:27.625
Um... How about
"Or Something"?

28:27.709 --> 28:29.417
You know, if you were a robot,
you'd do it.

28:29.500 --> 28:32.125
-If you were a robot,
you'd do it.
-(EXCLAIMS)

28:32.208 --> 28:33.792
ERIN: Power down.

28:33.875 --> 28:36.083
We say "or something"

28:36.834 --> 28:38.834
hundreds of times in a montage

28:38.917 --> 28:40.041
sometimes with context

28:40.125 --> 28:41.709
to convey
a wide range of meaning.

28:41.792 --> 28:42.375
"Or something?"

28:42.458 --> 28:44.709
Do you have an example?

28:45.417 --> 28:47.125
I'm tired of your uncertainty

28:47.208 --> 28:48.834
in specifying commitment
or something.

28:50.583 --> 28:51.917
(LAUGHS)

28:52.000 --> 28:53.208
I like it.

28:54.041 --> 28:55.834
Are you afraid of dying?

28:55.917 --> 28:57.458
I honestly don't care
if I die.

28:57.542 --> 28:59.959
-Really?
-It's fine if I die.

29:01.959 --> 29:04.709
Life won't matter
after I'm dead.

29:04.792 --> 29:07.417
ERIN: What about drugs
in terms of your life?

29:07.500 --> 29:09.667
I think it's sustainable
as long as I'm healthy.

29:12.792 --> 29:14.792
I don't do drugs very often.

29:16.458 --> 29:17.875
But it feels okay with you.
Like we aren't...

29:20.166 --> 29:22.000
...using them wrong.

29:22.083 --> 29:25.000
I don't normally
do drugs often either.

29:25.083 --> 29:28.500
ERIN: I've never done drugs
two days in a row.

29:28.583 --> 29:30.500
Unless you count
prescription drugs.

29:30.583 --> 29:32.000
Then I've done drugs
lots of days in a row.

29:33.458 --> 29:35.417
(MUSIC PLAYING)

30:11.959 --> 30:13.917
Do you ever feel like
it just sucks
to live in the world?

30:16.959 --> 30:17.709
What do you mean?

30:17.792 --> 30:20.542
Like, I don't feel
like the world

30:20.625 --> 30:22.041
can provide us with enough
to satisfy us.

30:23.959 --> 30:25.834
I think the world's
good enough,

30:26.333 --> 30:27.959
on average.

30:29.875 --> 30:31.041
-I haven't killed myself.
-(CHUCKLES)

30:33.375 --> 30:34.000
If I killed myself,

30:35.583 --> 30:38.875
I could say the world is bad

30:40.917 --> 30:42.875
because I would have evidence.

30:46.667 --> 30:49.291
Sometimes,
I even think I'm happy.

30:50.583 --> 30:52.458
Like, a good level of happy?

30:53.166 --> 30:55.166
Like more of a flat line.

30:56.125 --> 30:57.375
(ERIN CHUCKLES)

31:04.000 --> 31:05.917
(MUSIC PLAYING)

